<section id="command-butlast">
<title>BUTLAST</title>
<indexterm><primary>BUTLAST</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>BL</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>BUTLAST</command> <parameter>thing</parameter>
<command>BL</command> <parameter>thing</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
If the input is a word, BUTLAST outputs a word containing all but the last character of the input.
If the input is a list, BUTLAST outputs a list containing all but the last member of the input.
</para>

<para>
BUTLAST throws a bad input error if given the empty list, the empty string, or an array.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SHOW BUTLAST [1 2 3]</userinput>
[1 2]</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SHOW BUTLAST "Hello</userinput>
Hell</programlisting>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
